@@eThe Scorching Sands@@N

A superheated dune-sea and ember-basin complex in the east-southeastern
reaches of the desert corridor, the Scorching Sands are not simply
hot desert. They are a @@ylegal and ecological pressure chamber@@N where
failing institutions left behind route doctrine, ration rites, and
weaponized heat technology.

Four micro-zones define the terrain. The @@rEmber Dunes@@N are tall
red-gold ridges whose leeward pockets trap heat through the night.
The @@dKiln Basins@@N are blackened depressions where repeated ritual
firing events created permanent breath-burn hazards. The @@yCinder
Channels@@N follow former distributary cuts now used as convoy lanes --
wind-sheltered but ambush-prone. The @@WAshglass Rims@@N are transitional
belts of fused sand and brittle slag, geological precursors to the
Saltglass Reach's true Glasswind Belts.

In the age of the Salt Ledger Kingdoms, crown contractors built
@@ykiln houses@@N here to fire seal-ceramics and convoy fittings. Their
innovation was sun-fired verification clay: shipment tags that changed
color irreversibly when tampered with. This made the Sands a
@@Wfraud-resistant certification district@@N. The @@yBurn Ledger@@N -- a
semi-buried audit complex -- recorded kiln batches, water allotments,
and passage fees in one integrated archive.

The @@yScorch Clause@@N is a standard contract rider merchants still
invoke: supplemental water allocation for cargo in transit, mandatory
heat-certification of seal materials, and liability segmented by
route rather than total journey. It is one of the earliest legal
mechanisms anticipating the Saltglass Reach's maritime-style risk law.

Three factions hold ground. @@gEmber Wardens@@N descend from route
inspectors and kiln officers, maintaining shade stations and crossing
windows under the credo: "No crossing without measure." @@rAshbound
Reavers@@N track convoy heat fatigue and strike where water discipline
breaks down. The @@dCauterist Synod@@N interprets heat as purgative
truth, branding false seals as heresy and staging trial-by-sun rites
at abandoned kiln mouths.

Three daily heat phases govern survival: @@rHard Glare@@N at midday
brings surface burns and rapid dehydration; @@yBreathfire@@N in late
afternoon traps basin heat into inhalation risk; @@dFalse Mercy@@N at
night masks residual ground heat beneath apparent cooling.

Common sayings echo through graffiti and NPC speech alike:
@@d"Shade is borrowed law." "The sun sees the false seal first."@@N
